1
00:00:06,380 --> 00:00:07,580
You weren't...

2
00:00:09,520 --> 00:00:10,650
working, right?

3
00:00:12,620 --> 00:00:13,300
Zen!

4
00:00:15,450 --> 00:00:16,050
Ryo?

5
00:00:16,900 --> 00:00:17,440
Why...

6
00:00:18,350 --> 00:00:19,430
Why are you here?

7
00:00:31,880 --> 00:00:32,659
Zen...

8
00:00:36,230 --> 00:00:37,590
Stay over tonight.

9
00:00:38,840 --> 00:00:40,840
What's come over you all of a sudden?

10
00:00:42,930 --> 00:00:44,010
I missed you.

11
00:00:48,080 --> 00:00:49,440
I missed you too.

12
00:00:54,000 --> 00:00:55,420
I'm so cold.

13
00:00:57,320 --> 00:00:58,030
You idiot.

14
00:00:59,150 --> 00:01:00,210
Let's go upstairs.

15
00:01:02,130 --> 00:01:02,500
Mm.

16
00:02:01,630 --> 00:02:06,190
[Fake Fact Lips]

17
00:02:07,180 --> 00:02:11,540
[Final Episode: It's a Full Moon]

18
00:02:12,760 --> 00:02:13,590
Um,

19
00:02:14,010 --> 00:02:15,980
when I called you earlier,

20
00:02:16,579 --> 00:02:18,120
you said you were working.

21
00:02:19,400 --> 00:02:20,660
Were you at the office?

22
00:02:24,620 --> 00:02:25,870
Wait, is it for a guy?

23
00:02:26,270 --> 00:02:28,060
Well, well.

24
00:02:29,590 --> 00:02:30,329
Mm.

25
00:02:30,950 --> 00:02:32,100
I just stopped by.

26
00:02:36,600 --> 00:02:38,000
Why do you ask?

27
00:02:39,329 --> 00:02:39,920
Nothing.

28
00:02:41,720 --> 00:02:42,920
I just wanted to know.

29
00:02:45,930 --> 00:02:47,730
Hey, don't you think it's weird?

30
00:02:49,060 --> 00:02:49,440
What?

31
00:02:49,760 --> 00:02:51,620
You've been acting weird all day.

32
00:02:52,100 --> 00:02:53,740
Just say what's on your mind.

33
00:02:59,280 --> 00:03:00,140
What about you?

34
00:03:01,240 --> 00:03:01,750
Eh?

35
00:03:03,320 --> 00:03:05,450
Is there anything you want to say to me?

36
00:03:12,080 --> 00:03:13,220
It's always been me

37
00:03:15,390 --> 00:03:16,890
doing all the talking.

38
00:03:30,590 --> 00:03:32,050
You really do have a fever.

39
00:03:32,730 --> 00:03:34,290
No, I don't.

40
00:03:36,410 --> 00:03:39,130
You said you were cold earlier.
That's because of the fever, right?

41
00:03:39,130 --> 00:03:40,820
And you obviously don't have any energy.

42
00:03:40,820 --> 00:03:42,090
I already told you, I'm not.

43
00:03:42,090 --> 00:03:43,420
You must be tired then.

44
00:03:44,460 --> 00:03:45,790
You've been really busy

45
00:03:45,980 --> 00:03:47,100
at work lately too.

46
00:03:50,660 --> 00:03:52,250
I should probably head home today.

47
00:03:52,250 --> 00:03:53,980
With me here,
you probably can't rest properly.

48
00:03:53,980 --> 00:03:55,020
Wait.

49
00:03:55,050 --> 00:03:57,150
We have a trip the day after tomorrow.

50
00:03:57,790 --> 00:03:59,380
If you keep pushing yourself like this,
we won't be able to go.

51
00:03:59,380 --> 00:04:00,880
No, I'm not!

52
00:04:00,910 --> 00:04:02,640
All right. Just lie down, okay?

53
00:04:03,340 --> 00:04:05,340
Don't force yourself to come see me.

54
00:04:11,510 --> 00:04:12,590
I...

55
00:04:15,190 --> 00:04:17,589
still want to stay with you,
even like this.

56
00:04:18,250 --> 00:04:20,779
I want to treasure the time
we spend together.

57
00:04:23,890 --> 00:04:25,230
But you don't feel the same, right?

58
00:04:25,230 --> 00:04:27,130
No, I just

59
00:04:27,160 --> 00:04:28,600
want you to take better care of yourself.

60
00:04:28,600 --> 00:04:30,400
What's been going on with you
since earlier?

61
00:04:30,400 --> 00:04:31,340
Careful.

62
00:04:36,880 --> 00:04:38,290
I hate it

63
00:04:38,630 --> 00:04:41,200
when you don't tell me you're hurting.

64
00:04:44,490 --> 00:04:46,750
Aren't you hiding something from me too?

65
00:04:47,360 --> 00:04:48,150
What?

66
00:04:49,140 --> 00:04:50,260
I'm not hiding anything.

67
00:04:50,260 --> 00:04:50,840
Then...

68
00:04:56,360 --> 00:04:58,220
What about lying to me about being

69
00:04:59,650 --> 00:05:02,380
at the office
when you were actually with Futami?

70
00:05:07,800 --> 00:05:09,400
You're not even denying it.

71
00:05:11,160 --> 00:05:12,660
Zen...

72
00:05:16,220 --> 00:05:19,010
Are you happier
being with Futami than with me?

73
00:05:19,590 --> 00:05:20,220
You...

74
00:05:21,100 --> 00:05:24,230
Do you think something is going on
between Futami and me?

75
00:05:29,280 --> 00:05:31,450
Is that how little you trust me?

76
00:05:39,640 --> 00:05:41,920
You don't understand how I feel at all.

77
00:05:43,100 --> 00:05:44,840
How could I?

78
00:05:45,150 --> 00:05:46,560
You always act cool and composed

79
00:05:46,560 --> 00:05:49,420
and never let yourself be vulnerable
in front of me.

80
00:05:54,920 --> 00:05:55,870
I...

81
00:05:59,350 --> 00:06:01,060
hate not being needed by you

82
00:06:02,240 --> 00:06:04,440
even more than not being able to see you.

83
00:06:06,720 --> 00:06:08,790
You never tell me when you're upset.

84
00:06:13,930 --> 00:06:16,730
Right now, we're not equals
in this relationship.

85
00:06:19,160 --> 00:06:20,890
If things keep going like this,

86
00:06:22,380 --> 00:06:24,780
I don't think
I can continue being with you.

87
00:07:33,170 --> 00:07:34,940
He's been like that all day.

88
00:07:35,580 --> 00:07:36,140
Yeah.

89
00:07:37,080 --> 00:07:39,190
Did something go wrong with the project?

90
00:07:39,190 --> 00:07:41,200
Ah. Did he get yelled at
by the supervisor?

91
00:07:41,200 --> 00:07:42,480
That was you yesterday, wasn't it?

92
00:07:42,480 --> 00:07:43,200
Yeah.

93
00:07:44,050 --> 00:07:46,450
Mr. Shido would never get yelled at.

94
00:07:48,370 --> 00:07:49,330
Then...

95
00:07:49,909 --> 00:07:52,310
could it be something about his girlfriend

96
00:07:53,050 --> 00:07:54,380
or something like that?

97
00:07:54,820 --> 00:07:55,690
Why don't you go ask him?

98
00:07:55,690 --> 00:07:56,500
No, no, no.

99
00:07:56,530 --> 00:07:57,480
I can't do that.

100
00:07:57,510 --> 00:07:59,730
-What are you afraid of? Go.
-You go.

101
00:07:59,750 --> 00:08:01,390
Where is Mr. Iwao from Sales Section 1?

102
00:08:01,390 --> 00:08:03,030
This is not Section 1.

103
00:08:03,060 --> 00:08:04,090
Oh, it's not?

104
00:08:04,110 --> 00:08:04,980
It's on the other side.

105
00:08:04,980 --> 00:08:06,280
That way?

106
00:08:06,300 --> 00:08:06,780
Go through there...

107
00:08:06,780 --> 00:08:07,250
Okay.

108
00:08:07,270 --> 00:08:08,530
Um... are

109
00:08:08,550 --> 00:08:09,600
those documents for Section 1?

110
00:08:09,600 --> 00:08:10,630
Ah, yes.

111
00:08:11,020 --> 00:08:12,150
I'll take them over.

112
00:08:13,240 --> 00:08:14,000
Thank you.

113
00:08:24,380 --> 00:08:25,770
Ah, Mr. Shido?

114
00:08:27,710 --> 00:08:29,160
Oh, here.

115
00:08:29,610 --> 00:08:31,960
Ah. Sorry to make you
bring them all the way over.

116
00:08:31,960 --> 00:08:33,890
It's okay. I was passing by anyway.

117
00:08:33,990 --> 00:08:34,690
Hey,

118
00:08:34,990 --> 00:08:36,419
do you know where Yotsuya is?

119
00:08:36,419 --> 00:08:38,120
He took the day off.

120
00:08:38,140 --> 00:08:39,169
I heard he has a fever.

121
00:08:39,169 --> 00:08:40,640
Well, it's rare.

122
00:08:40,880 --> 00:08:41,960
He'd been talking excitedly for days

123
00:08:41,960 --> 00:08:44,330
about having something
to look forward to this weekend.

124
00:08:44,330 --> 00:08:45,840
I'm a bit worried.

125
00:08:47,810 --> 00:08:49,340
Well, I'll get back to work.

126
00:08:51,240 --> 00:08:52,620
Good work.

127
00:08:52,650 --> 00:08:54,720
Well, isn't that Yotsuya?

128
00:08:54,750 --> 00:08:55,280
Eh?

129
00:08:55,580 --> 00:08:57,190
Weren't you off today?

130
00:08:57,210 --> 00:08:59,080
I only took half the day off.

131
00:08:59,350 --> 00:09:01,160
I need to get off work on time,
so don't stop me.

132
00:09:01,160 --> 00:09:02,900
Are you feeling better?

133
00:09:03,230 --> 00:09:05,640
Yeah, more or less.

134
00:09:32,260 --> 00:09:36,770
[Meet me in the meeting room after work]

135
00:09:47,040 --> 00:09:49,160
Oh? Do you have a work dinner today?

136
00:09:49,180 --> 00:09:50,240
No, I'm going home.

137
00:09:50,360 --> 00:09:52,220
Huh? It's barely clock-out time.

138
00:09:52,290 --> 00:09:53,510
That's exactly why.

139
00:09:53,920 --> 00:09:56,070
You guys should get off work on time
once in a while too.

140
00:09:56,070 --> 00:09:57,920
Have a good evening.

141
00:10:01,950 --> 00:10:04,470
He must be feeling unwell.

142
00:10:05,120 --> 00:10:05,760
No.

143
00:10:06,550 --> 00:10:09,350
Maybe he's off to have a fight
with his girlfriend.

144
00:10:11,920 --> 00:10:12,570
Eh?

145
00:10:12,700 --> 00:10:13,250
Mm.

146
00:10:14,400 --> 00:10:15,730
What are you doing here?

147
00:10:16,350 --> 00:10:18,420
I was so busy after the meeting,

148
00:10:18,730 --> 00:10:20,790
and I didn't even have time to tidy up.

149
00:10:20,840 --> 00:10:22,320
Speaking of, why are you here?

150
00:10:22,320 --> 00:10:23,470
Nothing.

151
00:10:26,200 --> 00:10:26,860
Eh?

152
00:10:27,120 --> 00:10:28,580
Yotsuya, you're here too.

153
00:10:30,240 --> 00:10:32,390
The three of us are all here.

154
00:10:32,830 --> 00:10:33,280
Ah.

155
00:10:35,760 --> 00:10:37,610
Yotsuya, are you feeling okay?

156
00:10:37,640 --> 00:10:38,140
Eh?

157
00:10:39,190 --> 00:10:40,430
Are you sick?

158
00:10:40,450 --> 00:10:42,360
Um...

159
00:10:42,580 --> 00:10:44,330
I slept it off.

160
00:10:44,710 --> 00:10:46,910
I only took the morning off
just to be safe.

161
00:10:46,910 --> 00:10:48,280
Hmm.

162
00:10:49,160 --> 00:10:52,080
It's rare to see
both of you looking so down.

163
00:10:52,500 --> 00:10:52,960
What?

164
00:10:53,780 --> 00:10:54,600
This guy

165
00:10:54,640 --> 00:10:57,100
has been in a really low mood all day.

166
00:10:57,140 --> 00:10:58,710
He even scared the juniors.

167
00:10:59,180 --> 00:10:59,850
Ah.

168
00:11:00,820 --> 00:11:01,600
This

169
00:11:02,190 --> 00:11:03,720
suits me perfectly, right?

170
00:11:04,390 --> 00:11:06,050
I got it yesterday.

171
00:11:06,190 --> 00:11:08,450
I have to say, I've got pretty good taste.

172
00:11:08,450 --> 00:11:09,320
Yesterday?

173
00:11:09,940 --> 00:11:10,550
Yeah.

174
00:11:11,510 --> 00:11:13,640
I went shopping with Shido yesterday.

175
00:11:14,000 --> 00:11:14,980
What about you?

176
00:11:15,820 --> 00:11:19,320
But since you only just bought it,
you haven't given it to him yet, right?

177
00:11:19,320 --> 00:11:20,850
What are you talking about?

178
00:11:20,880 --> 00:11:21,840
I'm leaving.

179
00:11:21,860 --> 00:11:23,600
What are you playing dumb for?

180
00:11:23,910 --> 00:11:27,910
You said you needed to buy something
yesterday, so I went along with you.

181
00:11:28,370 --> 00:11:30,190
A present.

182
00:11:30,740 --> 00:11:32,740
You even said you hoped he'd like it.

183
00:11:33,500 --> 00:11:34,140
Eh?

184
00:11:34,750 --> 00:11:37,010
Anyway, what are you two even doing here?

185
00:11:39,860 --> 00:11:40,590
Right now...

186
00:11:41,010 --> 00:11:41,680
Hmm?

187
00:11:42,780 --> 00:11:44,510
Yesterday's gift shopping...

188
00:11:46,300 --> 00:11:48,060
You just spoiled the surprise.

189
00:11:49,320 --> 00:11:50,080
Eh?

190
00:11:52,670 --> 00:11:53,270
What?

191
00:11:58,550 --> 00:11:59,240
Hey!

192
00:11:59,930 --> 00:12:01,290
I'm really sorry.

193
00:12:01,310 --> 00:12:04,190
But since it's for Yotsuya,
you could've just told me beforehand.

194
00:12:04,190 --> 00:12:05,320
Then I could've

195
00:12:05,350 --> 00:12:06,600
helped you pick something out properly.

196
00:12:06,600 --> 00:12:07,380
Shut up.

197
00:12:08,170 --> 00:12:09,280
Stop talking.

198
00:12:10,370 --> 00:12:11,560
Come on.

199
00:12:11,590 --> 00:12:13,590
Sure, I messed up.

200
00:12:13,610 --> 00:12:15,830
But do you really need to be this angry?

201
00:12:16,090 --> 00:12:18,890
Seriously, did something happen
between you two?

202
00:12:21,270 --> 00:12:21,730
Well,

203
00:12:22,370 --> 00:12:24,180
normally, Shido,

204
00:12:24,200 --> 00:12:25,670
you wouldn't get this angry.

205
00:12:25,670 --> 00:12:27,060
You'd just fire back
with some cutting remark.

206
00:12:27,060 --> 00:12:28,830
Oh, no. Zen is just...

207
00:12:28,850 --> 00:12:29,490
Zen?

208
00:12:30,780 --> 00:12:32,440
Why are you calling him by his first name?

209
00:12:32,440 --> 00:12:33,460
Um... Well...

210
00:12:33,760 --> 00:12:34,820
More importantly,

211
00:12:34,910 --> 00:12:37,260
why did you buy Yotsuya a gift?

212
00:12:37,560 --> 00:12:38,560
Nothing.

213
00:12:39,230 --> 00:12:39,940
You two

214
00:12:40,200 --> 00:12:42,870
became so close when I wasn't around?

215
00:12:42,900 --> 00:12:43,760
It's so weird.

216
00:12:43,970 --> 00:12:44,700
Weren't you

217
00:12:44,730 --> 00:12:46,920
always butting heads before?

218
00:12:46,940 --> 00:12:48,290
Well, we're

219
00:12:48,310 --> 00:12:49,370
both adults now.

220
00:12:49,400 --> 00:12:50,300
I'd say we've mellowed out.

221
00:12:50,300 --> 00:12:51,990
No, it's still weird.

222
00:12:52,020 --> 00:12:54,030
Alright, even if I give you that,

223
00:12:54,370 --> 00:12:56,250
Yotsuya, you've always been

224
00:12:56,270 --> 00:12:57,930
friendly with people,
so I can understand that.

225
00:12:57,930 --> 00:12:59,040
Hey, I'm friendly too.

226
00:12:59,040 --> 00:13:01,800
No, Shido,

227
00:13:02,650 --> 00:13:05,450
for someone as stubborn as you
to change like this,

228
00:13:05,500 --> 00:13:07,360
something definitely happened.

229
00:13:08,920 --> 00:13:09,530
Wait,

230
00:13:10,570 --> 00:13:12,430
are you two more than just rivals?

231
00:13:15,600 --> 00:13:16,300
Shido,

232
00:13:17,530 --> 00:13:19,440
what is Yotsuya to you?

233
00:13:22,660 --> 00:13:24,090
Yotsuya is...

234
00:13:28,660 --> 00:13:29,260
Ryo is...

235
00:13:30,900 --> 00:13:32,160
-my boyfriend.
-What?

236
00:13:46,120 --> 00:13:47,320
No way.

237
00:13:50,820 --> 00:13:52,170
Seriously,

238
00:13:52,830 --> 00:13:54,350
why did you suddenly tell him?

239
00:13:54,350 --> 00:13:55,250
Sorry.

240
00:13:55,920 --> 00:13:58,170
That's because you're imagining things.

241
00:13:58,170 --> 00:13:59,450
Anyone would overthink it

242
00:13:59,450 --> 00:14:00,500
after seeing

243
00:14:00,520 --> 00:14:02,400
something that looked like a date.

244
00:14:02,400 --> 00:14:06,510
Do you really think anything could
ever happen between me and anyone else?

245
00:14:06,510 --> 00:14:07,220
Then,

246
00:14:08,230 --> 00:14:10,400
what was that sudden showdown

247
00:14:10,910 --> 00:14:12,030
with Futami about?

248
00:14:13,720 --> 00:14:14,610
That was...

249
00:14:17,940 --> 00:14:18,970
to see

250
00:14:18,990 --> 00:14:20,580
who was more worthy of being

251
00:14:20,900 --> 00:14:21,560
your rival.

252
00:14:22,360 --> 00:14:23,370
What?

253
00:14:25,100 --> 00:14:27,460
I couldn't help taking the bait.

254
00:14:36,000 --> 00:14:36,880
Then...

255
00:14:38,220 --> 00:14:39,920
you could've

256
00:14:40,510 --> 00:14:42,290
just told me about
that kind of showdown sooner.

257
00:14:42,290 --> 00:14:43,580
How could I?

258
00:14:44,540 --> 00:14:46,940
And you, struggling like that
all by yourself—

259
00:14:46,940 --> 00:14:48,650
you could've told me sooner too.

260
00:14:48,650 --> 00:14:50,440
How could I?

261
00:14:51,440 --> 00:14:53,170
Saying something as willful as

262
00:14:53,370 --> 00:14:55,460
"Only I can be
both your boyfriend and your rival..."

263
00:14:55,460 --> 00:14:56,270
Then

264
00:14:56,590 --> 00:14:58,870
what about all the willful things
I've said to you?

265
00:14:58,870 --> 00:15:00,080
That's fine.

266
00:15:00,460 --> 00:15:01,440
Because it's you.

267
00:15:01,440 --> 00:15:02,610
No, it's not.

268
00:15:03,170 --> 00:15:04,570
We're in a relationship,

269
00:15:04,920 --> 00:15:06,570
but only one of us has been holding back,

270
00:15:06,570 --> 00:15:10,230
and only one of us has been
making all the effort. That's not right.

271
00:15:10,740 --> 00:15:11,480
Well...

272
00:15:12,800 --> 00:15:14,460
I'm the reason you've ended up

273
00:15:14,980 --> 00:15:15,580
like this.

274
00:15:24,470 --> 00:15:26,800
I kept taking your affection for granted.

275
00:15:27,740 --> 00:15:31,800
Even though some feelings can't be
conveyed unless you say them out loud,

276
00:15:32,300 --> 00:15:33,960
I kept running away from that.

277
00:15:38,390 --> 00:15:39,670
So, I want to change.

278
00:15:40,980 --> 00:15:41,850
I don't want you

279
00:15:42,740 --> 00:15:44,940
to force yourself or hold back anymore.

280
00:15:46,330 --> 00:15:47,890
Rival or lover,

281
00:15:49,460 --> 00:15:51,810
there's only you. I hope you can trust me.

282
00:15:55,120 --> 00:15:55,740
Mm.

283
00:16:11,660 --> 00:16:12,700
I've been scared.

284
00:16:13,390 --> 00:16:13,900
What?

285
00:16:16,770 --> 00:16:20,370
I've been scared that my feeling of
wanting to be with you forever

286
00:16:21,130 --> 00:16:23,370
might become a burden to you.

287
00:16:24,970 --> 00:16:26,500
The more I thought about it,

288
00:16:27,130 --> 00:16:29,250
the more I lost my composure.

289
00:16:31,280 --> 00:16:33,880
Before I knew it,
I was already pushing myself.

290
00:16:36,030 --> 00:16:39,160
I didn't even realize

291
00:16:39,760 --> 00:16:41,960
that it was the same as not trusting you.

292
00:16:50,560 --> 00:16:51,590
I trust you,

293
00:16:52,520 --> 00:16:54,250
and everything about you, Zen.

294
00:16:55,110 --> 00:16:55,730
Ryo.

295
00:16:57,480 --> 00:16:59,410
From now on, I'll be honest with you

296
00:16:59,820 --> 00:17:00,750
about how I feel.

297
00:17:01,940 --> 00:17:02,950
Bring it on.

298
00:17:04,329 --> 00:17:05,760
Whether it's jealousy or anything else,

299
00:17:05,760 --> 00:17:07,040
I'll take it all.

300
00:17:07,800 --> 00:17:09,180
"Bring it on?"

301
00:17:10,230 --> 00:17:11,890
Is this another competition?

302
00:17:11,990 --> 00:17:13,910
This is our way, right?

303
00:17:15,329 --> 00:17:15,819
Well,

304
00:17:16,230 --> 00:17:18,160
let's call it a draw this time.

305
00:17:18,480 --> 00:17:19,339
No.

306
00:17:20,250 --> 00:17:21,359
You won.

307
00:17:24,040 --> 00:17:25,599
You've been

308
00:17:26,010 --> 00:17:28,339
showing me your cool side this whole time.

309
00:17:31,140 --> 00:17:32,950
But I'm very happy.

310
00:17:33,940 --> 00:17:36,300
You said I'm your boyfriend.

311
00:17:36,570 --> 00:17:37,700
Are you teasing me?

312
00:17:37,720 --> 00:17:38,820
No.

313
00:17:39,400 --> 00:17:41,020
You've always been cool.

314
00:17:41,930 --> 00:17:42,850
I think

315
00:17:42,880 --> 00:17:44,200
it's the first time
you've ever said that to me.

316
00:17:44,200 --> 00:17:45,120
That's because

317
00:17:45,140 --> 00:17:47,400
it's the first time I've said it out loud.

318
00:17:48,660 --> 00:17:50,120
I've always felt that way.

319
00:17:51,620 --> 00:17:52,690
That's why

320
00:17:53,110 --> 00:17:55,040
I want to stay by your side forever.

321
00:17:56,840 --> 00:17:57,340
Ryo!

322
00:17:59,700 --> 00:18:00,550
Yeah?

323
00:18:02,480 --> 00:18:03,090
I...

324
00:18:04,730 --> 00:18:06,370
I love you far more than

325
00:18:07,820 --> 00:18:08,570
you think...

326
00:18:08,590 --> 00:18:10,000
Aaaah!

327
00:18:10,020 --> 00:18:11,460
Oh no!

328
00:18:13,560 --> 00:18:15,750
Yes. Well, tomorrow afternoon...

329
00:18:16,120 --> 00:18:18,130
No, I'll find a way to finish it tonight.

330
00:18:18,130 --> 00:18:20,310
Yes, I'm very sorry!

331
00:18:20,930 --> 00:18:22,290
Yes. I'll hang up now.

332
00:18:23,160 --> 00:18:26,810
This is bad. I need to get back now.

333
00:18:30,210 --> 00:18:31,010
Even so...

334
00:18:32,770 --> 00:18:34,170
you still think I'm cool?

335
00:18:39,680 --> 00:18:40,260
Then...

336
00:18:42,030 --> 00:18:44,430
tell me the rest
when we're alone together.

337
00:19:04,270 --> 00:19:06,220
Are you really feeling okay now?

338
00:19:08,530 --> 00:19:09,220
Mm.

339
00:19:11,070 --> 00:19:13,220
I just overloaded myself with work.

340
00:19:14,710 --> 00:19:16,110
I was just tired.

341
00:19:16,540 --> 00:19:17,860
That's more like it.

342
00:19:25,100 --> 00:19:25,700
If I...

343
00:19:27,290 --> 00:19:30,220
couldn't prove
that I was worthy of being your rival,

344
00:19:31,740 --> 00:19:34,340
I was afraid
I wouldn't be able to be your lover.

345
00:19:36,050 --> 00:19:39,570
Since when did the man I chose
become so insecure?

346
00:19:39,930 --> 00:19:42,650
Whenever it comes to you,
I always get insecure.

347
00:19:44,030 --> 00:19:44,740
Why?

348
00:19:46,370 --> 00:19:47,900
Well, obviously...

349
00:19:51,510 --> 00:19:54,510
that's because I love you more.

350
00:19:58,100 --> 00:19:58,920
What?

351
00:20:00,140 --> 00:20:01,400
You don't understand.

352
00:20:01,470 --> 00:20:02,170
Eh?

353
00:20:03,310 --> 00:20:04,240
You

354
00:20:04,800 --> 00:20:06,200
don't understand at all.

355
00:20:07,330 --> 00:20:08,080
What?

356
00:20:09,820 --> 00:20:10,680
I...

357
00:20:11,980 --> 00:20:13,740
I love you

358
00:20:15,670 --> 00:20:17,230
far more than you think.

359
00:20:20,390 --> 00:20:23,190
It wasn't on a whim
that I became your lover.

360
00:20:25,660 --> 00:20:28,070
I also love you very much.

361
00:20:31,000 --> 00:20:32,320
I hope you know

362
00:20:34,030 --> 00:20:36,830
I've been trying so hard
because I love you so much.

363
00:20:41,880 --> 00:20:42,890
I love you so much.

364
00:20:46,430 --> 00:20:47,810
I'm sorry I couldn't

365
00:20:49,160 --> 00:20:50,170
say it before.

366
00:20:54,190 --> 00:20:55,350
What can I do

367
00:20:56,760 --> 00:20:58,960
to make you truly understand how I feel?

368
00:21:05,270 --> 00:21:06,600
This is already enough.

369
00:21:10,990 --> 00:21:11,660
Zen.

370
00:21:14,870 --> 00:21:16,670
I love you so much too.

371
00:21:20,630 --> 00:21:21,890
I know.

372
00:23:11,640 --> 00:23:12,280
Zen.

373
00:23:15,640 --> 00:23:16,390
Zen?

374
00:23:28,310 --> 00:23:29,490
Why are you smiling?

375
00:23:31,480 --> 00:23:32,230
Nothing.

376
00:23:33,180 --> 00:23:33,720
Here.

377
00:23:34,940 --> 00:23:35,440
Mm.

378
00:23:37,530 --> 00:23:39,330
Futami called a bunch of times.

379
00:23:39,350 --> 00:23:41,460
Ah, sorry.

380
00:23:41,980 --> 00:23:42,670
It's okay.

381
00:23:44,020 --> 00:23:46,350
I was going to tell him eventually anyway.

382
00:23:50,640 --> 00:23:51,570
It's a full moon.

383
00:23:55,550 --> 00:23:56,510
It is.

384
00:24:05,870 --> 00:24:07,450
"The moon is beautiful tonight"—

385
00:24:07,450 --> 00:24:08,360
don't you dare say that.

386
00:24:08,360 --> 00:24:10,530
I won't.

387
00:24:11,540 --> 00:24:13,550
I'll just say it directly.

388
00:24:16,090 --> 00:24:17,010
That I love you.

389
00:24:19,550 --> 00:24:21,930
Looks like we'll have good weather
for the trip tomorrow.

390
00:24:21,930 --> 00:24:23,040
Come on.

391
00:24:23,060 --> 00:24:24,390
Say it too.

392
00:24:33,780 --> 00:24:36,940
It's been a long time since we've
gotten to spend this much time together.

393
00:24:36,940 --> 00:24:37,720
I'm so happy.

394
00:24:42,840 --> 00:24:43,840
Somehow...

395
00:24:44,910 --> 00:24:46,940
I'm not quite used to this.

396
00:24:48,170 --> 00:24:49,060
What?

397
00:24:49,910 --> 00:24:51,050
Then I'll stop.

398
00:24:52,320 --> 00:24:53,330
Don't.

399
00:24:53,970 --> 00:24:54,750
Tell me.

400
00:24:56,580 --> 00:24:58,350
Because we've finally...

401
00:24:59,470 --> 00:25:01,500
By the way, what about your performance?

402
00:25:01,500 --> 00:25:02,360
Shut up!

403
00:25:02,390 --> 00:25:04,800
I came up with three more proposals
than this guy.

404
00:25:04,800 --> 00:25:07,120
Churning out useless proposals
is just wasted effort.

405
00:25:07,120 --> 00:25:07,570
Ah...

406
00:25:08,540 --> 00:25:09,670
Darn it.

407
00:25:09,690 --> 00:25:11,450
I'll just keep you company
while you sober up.

408
00:25:11,450 --> 00:25:13,430
Since I didn't bring the T-shirt,

409
00:25:13,780 --> 00:25:15,080
you could just head back home.

410
00:25:15,080 --> 00:25:16,360
College life without me around

411
00:25:16,360 --> 00:25:18,730
must be so dull for you.

412
00:25:19,690 --> 00:25:20,550
Keep dreaming.

413
00:25:22,430 --> 00:25:23,070
Bye.

414
00:25:37,520 --> 00:25:39,370
You've become honest.

415
00:25:41,280 --> 00:25:42,460
I knew it. I should just stop.

416
00:25:42,460 --> 00:25:43,830
Why?

417
00:25:43,850 --> 00:25:45,550
The mood just now was clearly
building up to an "I love you."

418
00:25:45,550 --> 00:25:47,640
I don't know anything about
those kinds of moods.

419
00:25:47,640 --> 00:25:48,490
If it's said too many times,

420
00:25:48,490 --> 00:25:49,770
it won't feel as special anymore.

421
00:25:49,770 --> 00:25:50,510
No.

422
00:25:50,530 --> 00:25:51,790
It won't.

423
00:25:53,100 --> 00:25:53,890
So...

